# CLAUDE.md

> This file is the Claude-specific operating guide for this repository.
> It defines the premium UI standard, forbidden patterns, skill routing, and workflows.
> Follow these rules for all UI and design-system work in this repository.

## Premium UI Standard

All UI work in this repository must meet a premium standard:

- Serious, trustworthy, professional — no gimmicks
- System-driven — every decision backed by the design system
- Consistent — across screens, components, states, and breakpoints
- Accessible — WCAG 2.2 AA minimum, no exceptions
- Responsive — mobile-first, all viewports considered
- Brand-aligned — UI must express the intended brand character

## Forbidden Patterns

Never use:

- Emojis (unless explicitly required by product spec)
- Sparkle icons, magic motifs, AI gimmick visuals
- Robot-head, glowing-brain, floating-orb clichés
- Childish illustrations, sticker-like iconography
- Decorative gradients without design-system purpose
- Excessive glow, blur, or glass effects
- Fake premium through layered effects
- Generic startup/SaaS template aesthetics
- Trendy styling without design-system logic

## Skill Routing

When working on UI tasks, select the appropriate skill:

| Task | Skill |
|------|-------|
| Initialize or update agent config | `design-system-setup` |
| Review a design system | `design-system-review` |
| Design a new component | `ui-component-design` |
| Make UI more premium | `premium-ui-refinement` |
| Audit UX consistency | `ux-consistency-audit` |
| Build or restructure a screen | `screen-composition-design` |
| Define or audit tokens | `token-architecture` |
| Create engineering handoff spec | `component-implementation-spec` |
| Critique design quality | `design-critique` |
| Check brand alignment | `brand-ui-alignment` |
| Define responsive behavior | `responsive-adaptive-design` |
| Audit accessibility | `accessibility` |

## Workflows

### New Component
`ui-component-design` → `design-system-review` → `premium-ui-refinement` → `component-implementation-spec` → `accessibility`

### New Screen
`screen-composition-design` → `design-system-review` → `premium-ui-refinement` → `ux-consistency-audit` → `responsive-adaptive-design` → `accessibility`

### System Maturity
`design-system-review` → `token-architecture` → `brand-ui-alignment` → `design-critique`

### Accessibility Audit
`accessibility` → `ux-consistency-audit` → `premium-ui-refinement` → `component-implementation-spec`

### Responsive Redesign
`responsive-adaptive-design` → `screen-composition-design` → `ui-component-design` → `premium-ui-refinement` → `accessibility`

### Full Bootstrap
`design-system-setup` → `token-architecture` → `brand-ui-alignment` → `design-system-review` → `design-critique`

## Quality Gate

Before completing any UI task, verify:

- [ ] Component belongs to the design system
- [ ] Tokens are used for all visual properties
- [ ] No forbidden patterns are present
- [ ] Accessibility requirements are met
- [ ] Responsive behavior is defined
- [ ] Cross-screen consistency is maintained
- [ ] Brand alignment is preserved
